lcan and algroup merged that year becoming alcan inc –edit pechiney became the wholly owned subsidiary of alcan in  after it was purchased in a deal worth  billion alcan spun off the majority of prepechiney rolling activities to create an independent company—novelis inc –edit the original rio tinto company was established in spain in  and became a worldwide copper producer by the end of the s today the rio tinto group is a britishaustralian multinational mining and resources group edit since may  constellium is listed on the new york stock exchange and nyse euronext market edit on october constellium announced the acquisition of wise metals a private aluminium sheet producer located in muscle shoals alabama usa the transaction diversified constellium’s global footprint and offerings by increasing the company’s exposure to the north american market wise’s growing can sheet business in the us will supplement constellium’s leading position in europe and provide stability through longterm contracts with global beverage can customers activitiesedit aerospace and transportationedit constelliums aerospace and transportation business unit has around  employees working at  sites in europe and america the company deliver aircraft parts and components for the commercial aircraft military and space sectors it offers a low density alloy for lighter aircraft named airware® this solution is a technology inspiring heightened interest among aerospace companies in using new aluminium solutions rather than composites for hightech structures in the next generation of aircraft packaging and automotive rolled productsedit constellium designs and produces aluminium products including packaging automotive industrial coil and sheet the unit has four plants and employs over  people automotive structures and industryedit constellium provides structures for european and north american car manufacturers and emerging markets in the global automotive sector from six sites in germany the us and china in parallel constellium also supplies diverse customized extrusions including soft and hard alloys and large profiles through ten sites in europe the unit employs over  people constellium and recyclingedit recycling has become very important in the aluminium industry and  of all aluminium produced since  is still in use today as part of its recycling programme constellium is a partner in the eu pamela project where it helped recycle the aluminium parts of a yearold twinaisle airbus a airplane  of the weight of the plane was aluminium which is fully recyclable and does not lose its properties when recycled constellium is a founding member of aluminium stewardship initiatives asi to promote responsible practices across the aluminium value chain it also joined in  the un global compact constellium worldwideedit constellium operates  production facilities throughout europe china and north and central america it employs approximately  people constellium has six main sites that supply its aerospace and transportation packaging and automotive rolled products and automotive structures and industry divisions in germany constelliums singen site has cold mills an integrated hotcold rolling line and one of the largest extrusion presses in the world in france constellium has eight sites among which neufbrisach and issoire neufbrisach houses a rolling mill an automotive finishing line and a recycling center issoire has one of the worlds two leading aerospace plate mills and largevolume recycling and inaugurated its airware® casthouse on march   the sierre site in switzerland has a dedicated precision plate shop for general engineering products in the usa ravenswood constellium has an aerospace plate shop with stretcher and widecoil capabilities referencesedit  httpwwwaluminiumtodaycomnewsviewconstelliumappointsnewceo  httpwwwconstelliumcomaluminiumcompanygovernanceexecutivecommittee  httpinreuterscomarticlerioalcanfranceidinldebdj  httpwwwparkersburgnewscompagecontentdetailid