utions automotive technology and services automotive structures manufacturing sites extrusions products technologies and services constellium technology center   business  solutions constellium is structured in  businesses aerospace and transportation packaging  automotive rolled products and automotive structures  industry markets aerospace commercial aircraft military aircraft space packaging food and beverage closures cosmetics foil packaging automotive crash management systems other safety components bodyinwhite structures bodyinwhite sheets heat exchangers tubes bars and profiles decorative uses sheets for equipment parts industry aluminum in electronics mechanical engineering aluminium molds semiconductors and flat panels profiles tubes and bars sheets for industrial use transportation rail bus power rail commercial vehicles leisure vehicles marine building solar energy sheets profiles tubes and bars renewable energy solar wind distribution sports and leisure defense military aircraft armored vehicles defense key products defense success story markets constellium develops innovative value added aluminium products and solutions for a broad scope of markets and applications innovation our vision aluminium innovation success stories airware® automotive body sheet specifications product portfolio innovations for crash management systems our technology center and services our technology networks and best practice councils partnerships innovation at constellium aluminium is more than a metal it is the material that takes the shape of our ideas  so that our ideas may shape the world sustainability life cycle of aluminium our role in the lifecycle of aluminium three essentials on aluminium recycling case studies  automotive parts and beverage cans people health and safety motivation and engagement skill development gender diversity community engagement our approach to aluminium recycling objectives and targets operations energy efficiency climate change preventing pollution reducing waste responsible business external recognitions materiality assessment managing sustainability ethical business practices engaging our suppliers in sustainability conflict minerals products customer satisfaction innovation ecodesign material safety data sheets constellium is committed to preserving our natural resources and wholeheartedly promotes aluminium recycling as part of our industrial strategies print home  candidates careers why should you join constellium every day our near  employees fuse their diverse talents experiences and ideas to develop and produce the worldleading aluminium products and solutions for which constellium is renownedas a newly independent company with a new direction and vision in place our company today offers you an unrivalled opportunity to help us shape and define our future form position and coursefrom production engineers to support functions we are seeking talented passionate and committed individuals who are as excited about the possibilities of aluminium as we arein this section you can find detailed overviews of our jobs browse our vacancies and apply as well as meet our human resources managers and read employee testimonials  constellium at a glance  constellium locations  why join constellium quick links  constellium at a glance  where we are  news and press releases  multimedia library  work with us constellium websites  constellium soft alloys europe  constellium hard and soft alloys czech republic  constellium ravenswood plants sellsite  ctec services  legal notice  rss feeds  site map  contact  constellium  aluminum applications lightweight corrosion resistant conductor  constellium websites  contact us follow us media news and press releases multimedia library literature   news  media access constellium news press releases pictures videos publications and presentations candidates discover our jobs production and processes research and development lean experts environment health and safety sales and mar