ve transportation defense packaging industry building renewable energy distribution sports and leisure constellium is a leading player in the supply of aluminium products and solutions to companies operating in some of the fastestdeveloping sectors of the global economysetting the standard for aluminium expertise and innovation aluminium is an indispensable material for the st century lightweight easily recyclable formable  fulfilling structural requirements and easy to handle aluminium conducts heat and electricity well and resists corrosionwe draw on decades of aluminium processing expertise and unequaled global delivery capabilities by creatively collaborating with customers in both developed and emerging economies we help them achieve results and compete in today’s challenging business climate customers benefit from synergies in rd and innovation between technologies optimized for different markets our cutting‑edge work in the aerospace field for example feeds into our work in many other marketswe currently operate in  exciting and diverse markets we aim to continue building on our core skills to achieve selective growth in mature markets and to lead a drive for expansion in emerging markets keyfactconstellium serves customers from its  production facilities  administrative and commercial sites and its technology center  last update  february  back to top quick links  constellium at a glance  where we are  news and press releases  multimedia library  work with us constellium websites  constellium soft alloys europe  constellium hard and soft alloys czech republic  constellium ravenswood plants sellsite  ctec services  legal notice  rss feeds  site map  contact  constellium  quality aluminum semiproducts manufacturing company  constellium constellium uses cookies in order to analyze the frequentation rate of its website or interactions with social networks by pursuing your navigation you accept the use of these cookies for further information about the use of cookies or the opposition proceedings click here   constellium websites  contact us follow us media news and press releases multimedia library literature   news  media access constellium news press releases pictures videos publications and presentations candidates discover our jobs production and processes research and development lean experts environment health and safety sales and marketing support functions work with us why join constellium constellium job offers how to join constellium constellium university meet us students and apprentices graduates experts   careers join constellium to take full advantage of the opportunities that aluminium presents investors financial results and presentation earnings results annual and interim reports investor presentations analyst day regulatory filings stock price cstm investors contact     about constellium who we are industrial platform our locations děčín czech republic issoire france muscle shoals usa neufbrisach france ravenswood usa singen germany valais switzerland corporate governance board of directors executive committee annual general meetings about aluminium glossary finance financial results and presentation regulatory filings stock price cstm investors contact what we do environment health and safety ehs about constellium a global leader in aluminium transformation constellium designs and manufactures innovative and high valueadded aluminium products and components business  solutions aerospace and transportation products services brands markets research and innovation standards and certifications manufacturing sites packaging and automotive rolled products sheets and coils functional surfaces innovation in sheets  coils sustainability manufacturing sites automotive structures and industry automotive system solutions automotive technology and services automotive structures manufacturing sites extrusions products technologies and services constellium technology center   business  solutions constellium is structured in  businesses aerospace and transportation packaging  automotive rolled products and automotive structures  industry markets aerospace commercial aircraft military aircraft space packaging food and beverage closures cosmetics foil packaging automotive crash management systems other safety components bodyinwhite structures bodyinwhite sheets heat exchangers tubes bars and profiles decorative uses sheets for equipment parts industry aluminum in electronics mechanical engineering aluminium molds semiconductors and flat panels profiles tubes and bars sheets for industrial use transportation rail bus power rail commercial vehicles leisure vehicles marine building solar energy sheets profiles tubes and bars renewable energy solar wind distribution sports and leisure defense military aircraft armored vehicles defense key products defense success story markets constellium develops innovative value added aluminium products and solutions for a broad scope of markets and applications innovation our vision aluminium innovation success stories airware® automotive body sheet specifications product portfolio innovations for crash management systems our technology center and services our technology networks and best practice councils partnerships innovation at constellium aluminium is more than a metal it is the material that takes the shape of our ideas  so that our ideas may shape the world sustainability life cycle of aluminium our role in the lifecycle of aluminium three essentials on aluminium recycling case studies  automotive parts and beverage cans people health and safety motivation and engagement skill development gender diversity community engagement our approach to aluminium recycling objectives and targets operations energy efficiency climate change preventing pollution reducing waste responsible business external recognitions materiality assessment managing sustainability ethical business practices engaging our suppliers in sustainability conflict minerals products customer satisfaction innovation ecodesign material safety data sheets constellium is committed to preserving our natural resources and wholeheartedly promotes aluminium recycling as part of our industrial strategies constellium second quarter  earnings results to access earnings results page please click here spotlight download the business and sustainability performance report  click here to access news thursday  july  constellium reports second quarter  financial results tuesday  july  constellium to showcase extensive offering of bright and functional surfaces at aluminium china  thursday  july  constellium supplies  millionth part to ford motor company and expands to include the allnew ford expedition monday  july  constellium to report second quarter  results on july   tuesday  june  constellium to showcase its aluminium bright surfaces and its d app at the  automotive interiors expo all news our markets aerospace automotive transportation defense packaging industry building renewable energy distribution sports and leisure quick links  constellium at a glance  where we are  news and press releases  multimedia library  work with us constellium websites  constellium soft alloys europe  constellium hard and soft alloys czech republic  constellium ravenswood plants sellsite  ctec services  legal notice  rss feeds  site map  contact  constellium  constellium  wikipedia constellium from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search constellium traded as nyse cstm and euronext paris industry aluminium production founded  headquarters amsterdam netherlands key people jeanmarc germain ceo  peter matt cfo website httpwwwconstelliumcom constellium is a global producer of aluminium semiproducts with headquarters in amsterdam netherlands it was created when rio tinto sold off alcan engineered products to apollo management  and fsi  in  alcan engineered products was the result of various mergers and acquisitions between pechiney alcan and alusuisse constellium is listed on the new york stock exchange and euronext paris since may  it has a board of ten directors and maintain a onetier board of directors consisting of both executive directors and nonexecutive directors each a “director” under dutch law the board of directors is responsible for the policy and daytoday management the nonexecutive directors supervise and provide guidance to the executive directors constellium manufactures aluminium rolled products and extruded products based on a large variety of advanced alloys it has customers in different industries including mainly aerospace automotive and packaging sectors constellium reported € billion in revenues in  contents  company history  –  –  –  –      activities  aerospace and transportation  packaging and automotive rolled products  automotive structures and industry  constellium and recycling  constellium worldwide  references  external links company historyedit –edit henri merle et compagnie was founded in  in france it originally produced caustic soda from coal salt pyrites and limestone but also began producing aluminium metal in  the northern aluminium company ltd was founded in canada in  as a canadian subsidiary of the pittsburgh reduction company later called alcoa in  it was renamed aluminium company of canada in  and separated from alcoa in  becoming aluminium of canada ltd or alcan –edit henri merle et compagnie was renamed pechiney in  growing to become one of the worlds leading aluminium manufacturers in  pechiney announced that it had agreed to join in a merger with canadas alcan and switzerlands algroup to form a new globally operating aluminium producer which with sales worth nearly  billion became a player in the industry ahead of american company alcoa however the merger bumped up against european commission demands that alcan sell its interests in a german aluminium producer alunorf alcan refused to sell and pechiney was forced to withdraw from the merger alcan and algroup merged that year becoming alcan inc –edit pechiney became the wholly owned subsidiary of alcan in  after it was purchased in a deal worth  billion alcan spun off the majority of prepechiney rolling activities to create an independent company—novelis inc –edit the original rio tinto company was established in spain in  and became a worldwide copper producer by the end of the s today the rio tinto group is a britishaustralian multinational mining and resources group edit since may  constellium is listed on the new york stock exchange and nyse euronext market edit on october constellium announced the acquisition of wise metals a private aluminium sheet producer located in muscle shoals alabama usa the transaction diversified constellium’s global footprint and offerings by increasing the company’s exposure to the north american market wise’s growing can sheet business in the us will supplement constellium’s leading position in europe and provide stability through longterm contracts with global beverage can customers activitiesedit aerospace and transportationedit constelliums aerospace and transportation business unit has around  employees working at  sites in europe and america the company deliver aircraft parts and components for the commercial aircraft military and space sectors it offers a low density alloy for lighter aircraft named airware® this solution is a technology inspiring heightened interest among aerospace companies in using new aluminium solutions rather than composites for hightech structures in the next generation of aircraft packaging and automotive rolled productsedit constellium designs and produces aluminium products including packaging automotive industrial coil and sheet the unit has four plants and employs over  people automotive structures and industryedit constellium provides structures for european and north american car manufacturers and emerging markets in the global automotive sector from six sites in germany the us and china in parallel constellium also supplies diverse customized extrusions including soft and hard alloys and large profiles through ten sites in europe the unit employs over  people constellium and recyclingedit recycling has become very important in the aluminium industry and  of all aluminium produced since  is still in use today as part of its recycling programme constellium is a partner in the eu pamela project where it helped recycle the aluminium parts of a yearold twinaisle airbus a airplane  of the weight of the plane was aluminium which is fully recyclable and does not lose its properties when recycled constellium is a founding member of aluminium stewardship initiatives asi to promote responsible practices across the aluminium value chain it also joined in  the un global compact constellium worldwideedit constellium operates  production facilities throughout europe china and north and central america it employs approximately  people constellium has six main sites that supply its aerospace and transportation packaging and automotive rolled products and automotive structures and industry divisions in germany constelliums singen site has cold mills an integrated hotcold rolling line and one of the largest extrusion presses in the world in france constellium has eight sites among which neufbrisach and issoire neufbrisach houses a rolling mill an automotive finishing line and a recycling center issoire has one of the worlds two leading aerospace plate mills and largevolume recycling and inaugurated its airware® casthouse on march   the sierre site in switzerland has a dedicated precision plate shop for general engineering products in the usa ravenswood constellium has an aerospace plate shop with stretcher and widecoil capabilities referencesedit  httpwwwaluminiumtodaycomnewsviewconstelliumappointsnewceo  httpwwwconstelliumcomaluminiumcompanygovernanceexecutivecommittee  httpinreuterscomarticlerioalcanfranceidinldebdj  httpwwwparkersburgnewscompagecontentdetailidapollobuyspartofalcanhtmlnav  httpw