tive directors and nonexecutive directors each a “director” under dutch law the board of directors is responsible for the policy and daytoday management the nonexecutive directors supervise and provide guidance to the executive directors constellium manufactures aluminium rolled products and extruded products based on a large variety of advanced alloys it has customers in different industries including mainly aerospace automotive and packaging sectors constellium reported € billion in revenues in  contents  company history  –  –  –  –      activities  aerospace and transportation  packaging and automotive rolled products  automotive structures and industry  constellium and recycling  constellium worldwide  references  external links company historyedit –edit henri merle et compagnie was founded in  in france it originally produced caustic soda from coal salt pyrites and limestone but also began producing aluminium metal in  the northern aluminium company ltd was founded in canada in  as a canadian subsidiary of the pittsburgh reduction company later called alcoa in  it was renamed aluminium company of canada in  and separated from alcoa in  becoming aluminium of canada ltd or alcan –edit henri merle et compagnie was renamed pechiney in  growing to become one of the worlds leading aluminium manufacturers in  pechiney announced that it had agreed to join in a merger with canadas alcan and switzerlands algroup to form a new globally operating aluminium producer which with sales worth nearly  billion became a player in the industry ahead of american company alcoa however the merger bumped up against european commission demands that alcan sell its interests in a german aluminium producer alunorf alcan refused to sell and pechiney was forced to withdraw from the merger alcan and algroup merged that year becoming alcan inc –edit pechiney became the wholly owned subsidiary of alcan in  after it was purchased in a deal worth  billion alcan spun off the majority of prepechiney rolling activities to create an independent company—novelis inc –edit the original rio tinto company was established in spain in  and became a worldwide copper producer by the end of the s today the rio tinto group is a britishaustralian multinational mining and resources group edit since may  constellium is listed on the new york stock exchange and nyse euronext market edit on october constellium announced the acquisition of wise metals a private aluminium sheet producer located in muscle shoals alabama usa the transaction diversified constellium’s global footprint and offerings by increasing the company’s exposure to the north american market wise’s growing can sheet business in the us will supplement constellium’s leading position in europe and provide stability through longterm contracts with global beverage can customers activitiesedit aerospace and transportationedit constelliums aerospace and transportation business unit has around  employees working at  sites in europe and america the company deliver aircraft parts and components for the commercial aircraft military and space sectors it offers a low density alloy for lighter aircraft named airware® this solution is a technology inspiring heightened interest among aerospace companies in using new aluminium solutions rather than composites for hightech structures in the next generation of aircraft packaging and automotive rolled productsedit constellium designs and produces aluminium products including packaging automotive industrial coil and sheet the unit has four plants and employs over  people automotive structures and industryedit constellium provides structures for european and north american car manufacturers and emerging markets in the global automotive sector from six sites in germany the us and china in parallel constellium also supplies diverse customized extrusions including soft and hard alloys and large profiles through ten sites in europe the unit employs over  people constellium and recyclingedit recycling has become very important in the aluminium industry and  of all aluminium produced since  is still in use today as part of its recycling programme constellium is a partner in the eu pamela project where it helped recycle the aluminium parts of a yearold twinaisle airbus a airplane  of the weight of the plane was aluminium which is fully recyclable and does not lose its properties when recycled constellium is a founding member of aluminium stewardship initiatives asi to promote responsible practices across the aluminium value chain it also joined in  the un global compact constellium worldwideedit constellium operates  production facilities throughout europe china and north and central america it employs approximately  people constellium has six main sites that supply its aerospace and transportation packaging and automotive rolled products and automotive structures and industry divisions in germany constelliums singen site has cold mills an integrated hotcold rolling line and one of the largest extrusion presses in the world in france constellium has eight sites among which neufbrisach and issoire neufbrisach houses a rolling mill an automotive finishing line and a recycling center issoire has one of the worlds two leading aerospace plate mills and largevolume recycling and inaugurated its airware® casthouse on march   the sierre site in switzerland has a dedicated precision plate shop for general engineering products in the usa ravenswood constellium has an aerospace plate shop with stretcher and widecoil capabilities referencesedit  httpwwwaluminiumtodaycomnewsviewconstelliumappointsnewceo  httpwwwconstelliumcomaluminiumcompanygovernanceexecutivecommittee  httpinreuterscomarticlerioalcanfranceidinldebdj  httpwwwparkersburgnewscompagecontentdetailidapollobuyspartofalcanhtmlnav  httpwwwnasdaqcomarticleconstelliumpricesipoatbelowtherangecm  httpwwwconstelliumcomaluminiumcompanygovernance  httpwwwprnewswirecomnewsreleasesconstelliumreportsfullyearandfou